
                                            The striding men rally was held yesterday where the women's department in government handed over cheques to various NGO's to support their causes.

                                         JOHANNESBURG - Organizers of the ‘Stride for Good’ march held at the Nelson Mandela Bridge say they still have more plans ahead. The striding men rally led by whisky label Jonnie Walker South Africa was held yesterday where the women's department in government handed over cheques to various NGO's to support their causes. More than 300 NGO's and partners were involved. Brand unit manager Craig Button said, “The team has been working hard behind the scenes on social media, driving the message home about what the march is about.”